From: AsteroidOS Build System <build@asteroidos.org>
Date: Mon, 1 Jan 2024 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Drop REQUIRED from ecm_find_qmlmodule(QtQuick.VirtualKeyboard)

Upstream-Status: Inappropriate [OE-specific]

In cross-compilation the native qmlplugindump cannot dlopen the
ARM VirtualKeyboard plugin (wrong ELF arch) and always exits 3.
This makes ecm_find_qmlmodule report the module as missing and abort
the configure step with REQUIRED set.

Remove REQUIRED so the configure step can proceed.  Runtime
availability of qtvirtualkeyboard is enforced by RDEPENDS in the
Yocto recipe.
---
 CMakeLists.txt | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/CMakeLists.txt b/CMakeLists.txt
index 1234567..abcdefg 100644
--- a/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -42,7 +42,7 @@ else()
     endif()
 endif()
 
-ecm_find_qmlmodule(QtQuick.VirtualKeyboard 2.1 REQUIRED)
+ecm_find_qmlmodule(QtQuick.VirtualKeyboard 2.1)
 
 if (WITH_CMAKE_MODULES)
 # Install CMake modules
